 					http://www.history.com/news/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/tectiform.jpg
                    
					While most flutings are meandering lines, some hut-like figures called tectiforms, which are thought to have held symbolic meaning for the hunter-gather groups that inhabited the region some 13,000 years ago. (Credit: Jessica Cooney/Leslie Van Gelder)
